\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish mandatory technical and procedural controls for the protection of Elko County information systems during transmission and storage.
 This policy mandates the implementation of boundary protection,
 cryptographic standards,
 and architectural isolation to ensure the confidentiality,
 integrity,
 and availability of County data against internal and external threats.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Elko County Information Operations (ECIO) personnel,
 employees,
 contractors,
 vendors,
 and volunteers,
 and all information systems,
 networks,
 and infrastructure owned,
 leased,
 or operated by Elko County.
 This specifically includes:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Boundary Components
\series default
:
 Firewalls,
 routers,
 switches,
 and gateways.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Cryptographic Components
\series default
:
 Encryption keys,
 certificates,
 and modules.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Communication Channels
\series default
:
 VoIP,
 VPNs,
 and wireless networks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Protected Data
\series default
:
 CJI,
 Personally Identifiable Information (PII),
 and Restricted County records.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as the Authorizing Official (AO) for the County’s security architecture.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall approve in writing all ingress/egress traffic policy changes that deviate from the "Deny-by-Default" standard.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall authorize all connections to external information systems via formal Interconnection Security Agreements.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Network Administrator
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall configure and maintain boundary protection devices to enforce "Deny-by-Default" traffic policies.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall implement and verify network segregation between public,
 internal,
 and CJI-dedicated network segments (DMZ implementation).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall review firewall rule sets monthly to ensure no unauthorized access points exist.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Systems Administrator
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall configure encryption for data in-transit and at-rest using only FIPS-validated cryptographic modules.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall manage cryptographic keys in accordance with Section 6.4.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall disable split tunneling on all remote access endpoints.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All Users
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall use only County-authorized methods for remote access and data transmission.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall physically disconnect or disable collaborative computing devices (e.g.,
 webcams,
 microphones) when accessing CJI,
 unless the device is authorized for specific operational use.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Mandatory Enforcement
\series default
 - Personnel and systems must comply with the requirements defined herein.
 Failure to comply shall result in:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Immediate disconnection of the non-compliant system from the County network.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Revocation of administrative privileges where applicable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Disciplinary action up to and including termination of employment and referral to law enforcement for statutory violations (e.g.,
 NRS 205.4765).
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\end_layout

